<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> approved a drought relief bill totaling $ 6 billion, including a $ 145 million benefit pushed by dairy-state lawmakers for milk producers. Also Tuesday, a report by the <ORGANIZATION> Joint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agricultural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Facility </ORGANIZATION> said rains have relieved `` drought stress'' in parts of the Corn Belt, but crops have shown little improvement. Soybean futures prices plunged for the seventh straight day.
