</PERSON> with the requisite state of mind for a gratuities violation.'' However, <PERSON> McKay </PERSON> said <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> should have been sensitive to the possibility that <PERSON> Wallach </PERSON>'s motivation was to show appreciation for official activities benefiting him.
